# <type>: <subject>

# <body>

# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat     (new feature)
# * fix      (bug fix)
# * docs     (changes to documentation)
# * style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
# * refactor (refactoring production code)
# * test     (adding tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
# * chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
# * perf     (performance improvements)
# * ci       (CI configuration)

# Subject should use imperative tone and say what you did.
# The body should go into detail about changes made.
# The footer should contain any issue references or breaking changes.

# Example:
# feat: add LinkedIn OAuth integration
#
# - Implemented OAuth2 flow for LinkedIn authentication
# - Added profile data extraction from LinkedIn API
# - Created unified resume parser for LinkedIn data
#
# Closes #123